company.taskMan

Class Branch

  • java.lang.Object
    • company.taskMan.Branch

  • public class Branch
extends java.lang.Object
    The Main System that keeps track of the list of projects and the current Time. The Branch is also responsible of maintaining a resource manager (which in turn is responsible for managing the resources of the system). A Branch is located in a specific geographical location. For inter-branch communication, a specialized branch representative is appointed.
    Author:
    Tim Van den Broecke, Joran Van de Woestijne, Vincent Van Gestel and Eli Vangrieken

              throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,

        Throws:

      • planRawTask

        public void planRawTask(ProjectView project,
                        TaskView task,
                        java.time.LocalDateTime plannedStartTime,
                        java.util.List<ResourceView> concRes,
                        java.util.List<ResourceView> devs)
                 throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                        java.lang.IllegalStateException,
                        ResourceUnavailableException
        Plan a task in the system from a given start time. Reservations will be made for all the required resources and the developers will be assigned. It is however possible that this planning will conflict with other plannings in the system. It is the responsibility of the user when applying this method to check for conflicts using the findConflictingPlannings and handle these conflicts appropriately. If you want to be sure to not get into an inconsistent state, use planTask instead.
        Parameters:
        project - | The project the task belongs to
        task - | The task to plan
        plannedStartTime - | The planned begin time
        concRes - | The resources to plan
        devs - | The developers to assign
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - | If the supplied arguments are invalid
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - | If the planning would create an inconsistent system state
        ResourceUnavailableException - | If a required resource is unavailable for reservation
